\;y=2\;
\;y=2a\;
\begin{align*}(1)\;\;x=P_x&=AC=A_x\;,\;\;C=(0,2a)\\{}\\ \text{since} \;\Delta OEB\sim\Delta BPA\;,\;\sin t=\frac{AP}{AB}\implies (2)\;\;y= P_y&=2a-AP=2a-AB\sin t\\{}\\\text{By similarity or directly by Thales:}\;\;(3)\;\;AB\cdot AO&=AC^2 \end{align*}
2a\cot t=2a\frac{A_x}{A_y}=2a\frac{A_x}{2a}=A_x=x
AB=\frac{x^2}{AO}=\frac{x^2}{\frac x{\cos t}}= x\cos t=2a\cot t\cos t=2a\frac{\cos^2t}{\sin t}
y=2a-AB\sin t=2a\left(1-\cos^2t\right)\;\ldots
